-- ── Demio ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Demio is a browser-based webinar platform for marketers, offering live, automated, and evergreen webinars with built-in engagement tools and analytics.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription with free trial$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$45/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Seattle, Washington, USA (Banzai International, Inc.)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Demio: Browser-Based Webinar Software for Marketers$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Demio is a no-download webinar platform offering live, automated, and evergreen webinars with engagement tools. Plans start around $45/month, 14-day trial.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Demio is a browser-based webinar hosting platform built specifically for marketing teams that want to run live, automated, and evergreen ('recurring/on-demand') webinars without asking attendees to download any software. The product was launched in 2014-2015 by co-founders Wyatt Jozwowski and David Abrams, who built Demio to address what they identified as a persistent problem in the webinar-software market at the time: existing platforms were clunky, required desktop downloads or plugins, and created technical friction for both hosts and attendees that hurt registration-to-attendance conversion rates for marketing webinars. Demio operated as an independent, standalone SaaS company through the 2010s before being acquired in early 2021 by Banzai International, Inc., a Seattle-area marketing-technology holding company; Demio is now one of several branded products under the Banzai umbrella, alongside other demand-generation and event-marketing tools, and Banzai itself is a publicly traded company (listed as BNZI).

The core product design philosophy behind Demio is a fully in-browser experience -- hosts create a webinar 'room,' configure registration pages and reminder emails, and both hosts and attendees join the live session directly through a web browser with no app installation, a design choice aimed squarely at maximizing attendee show-up rates by removing friction at the moment someone clicks the join link. Within the room, Demio provides interactive engagement tools including live polls, a chat panel, a dedicated Q&A queue, downloadable handouts, audience reactions, and a feature called 'Featured Actions,' which lets hosts surface a call-to-action, offer, or resource directly inside the webinar player at a chosen moment (for example, pushing a special pricing link partway through a product demo webinar). Beyond live sessions, Demio supports Automated and Evergreen webinars -- pre-recorded sessions that play back on a schedule or on-demand, simulating a live experience (including simulated live chat) so that marketing teams can keep a high-performing webinar generating leads long after the original live delivery, a category of feature commonly associated with evergreen webinar funnel marketing tactics. Demio also provides registration-source tracking, integrations with common marketing and CRM tools (for pushing registrant and attendee data into email and marketing-automation platforms), and post-webinar analytics covering attendance, engagement, and drop-off.

Demio's pricing is structured in tiers gated by both room capacity (maximum simultaneous attendees) and feature access. The entry-level Starter plan is aimed at teams running occasional webinars for smaller audiences (commonly cited around a 50-attendee room with one host) with pricing beginning around $45 per month when billed annually. The Growth plan, generally cited starting around $75 per host per month (billed annually) for a larger room size (around 150 attendees), is positioned for companies running webinars more frequently as a core part of their marketing motion, and is the tier at which several of Demio's most requested capabilities unlock -- notably Automated/Evergreen webinars, registration-source-level analytics, and deeper custom branding controls, meaning teams that need automation specifically should budget for Growth rather than Starter. Larger attendee-capacity and multi-host requirements push customers into higher, more custom-priced tiers. A 14-day free trial is available across plans, letting prospective customers test the live-webinar experience before committing to a paid tier.

Demio's target users are marketing teams -- demand generation, product marketing, and customer-education functions -- at B2B SaaS and services companies that run webinars as a recurring lead-generation and nurture channel, rather than large broadcast-scale corporate town halls or massive public conferences, which tend to be better served by platforms designed for much higher attendee ceilings. Its most direct competitors in the marketing-webinar category include Zoom Webinars/Zoom Events, WebinarJam and its evergreen-focused sibling EverWebinar, GoTo Webinar, Livestorm, and BigMarker, with EverWebinar in particular being a frequent direct comparison point given its dedicated focus on evergreen/automated webinar funnels. Demio differentiates itself primarily on its no-download, fully browser-based attendee experience, its polished built-in engagement toolkit (Featured Actions, reactions, live Q&A), and its positioning as being purpose-built for marketers rather than IT/enterprise-communications teams, in contrast to broader video-conferencing platforms like Zoom that added webinar features on top of a general video-calling product. Since being folded into Banzai International's product suite, Demio has increasingly been sold and cross-promoted alongside Banzai's other demand-generation tools, reflecting a broader strategy of bundling webinar hosting with adjacent marketing-technology capabilities for B2B marketing teams.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '4414714c-18c2-421d-a443-5f73b6e567de';

